    <div class="info">
      <h2 class="title">VISHNUPAD TEMPLE</h2>
      <p class="desc">
        Vishnupad Temple is one of the most sacred Hindu temples, located on the banks of the **Phalgu River** in **Gaya, Bihar**. This ancient temple is believed to be built on the exact spot where **Lord Vishnu** left his footprint while subduing a demon.
      </p>
      <p class="desc">
        The footprint, about 40 cm long, is enshrined in a **basalt rock** inside the sanctum sanctorum. Devotees from across India visit the temple to perform **Pind Daan rituals** for their ancestors, especially during the holy period of **Pitru Paksha**.
      </p>
      <p class="desc">
        The current temple structure was rebuilt in the 18th century by **Ahilyabai Holkar**, the queen of Indore. It is made entirely of gray granite and stands as a symbol of devotion and legacy.
      </p>

